div.p:
Find these two auxiliary quantities, viz. an angle P, and the tangent of an angle
                    Q (of which only the logarithm is required), such, that sin. L tan. D tan. 1 =;
                    rad.

The angle API, expressed in time, is half the period the sun shines on the plane;
                    and the hour angle HPI, in time, is the interval between noon and the sun’s
                    leaving the plane.

Note. About noon the hour will be shown with uncertainty;
                    this is an inconvenience inseparable from all dials that show the hour by the
                    sun’s altitude.
